g how their work with blood reflects the social, cultural, and political dynamics of modern Malaysia. Carsten follows hospital workers into factories and community halls on blood drives and brings readers into the operating theater as a machine circulates a bypass patient's blood. Throughout, she foregrounds blood's symbolic power, uncovering the processes that make the hospital, the blood bank, the lab, and science itself work. In this way, blood becomes a privileged lens for understanding the entanglements of modern life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Sep 2020) 0aBlood donorszMalaysiazPulau Pinang (State) 0aBlood donorszMalaysiazPulau Pinang (State). 0aBloodxCollection and preservationzMalaysiazPulau Pinang (State) 0aBloodxCollection and preservationzMalaysiazPulau Pinang (State). 0aBloodxReligious aspects. 0aBloodxSocial aspectszMalaysiazPulau Pinang (State) 0aBloodxSocial aspectszMalaysiazPulau Pinang (State). 0aBloodxSymbolic aspects. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK eBook-Package 2019z978311069632540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478005698zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478005698423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781478005698.jpg  a978-3-11-069632-5  DUK eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles